gomodel:SYNGO_5479  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: electron microscopy showed B-raf (BRAF) was enriched in dendritic spines of rat hippocampus and neocortex. Subsynaptically, it was observed in the PSD, spine apparatus and throughout the dendritic spine.. Experimental description: \"Four male Wistar rats (130 g) were anesthetized with pentobarbital (40 mg/kg) and ...\"\n\nto confirm authors targeted the B-raf protein we annotated;\n\"Our immunoblotting experiments revealed a 95 kDa molecule, which we tentatively identified as the B-raf protein. This 95 kDa form is also predominant in mouse kidney (Kolch et al., unpublished data), and is presumably the product of an alternate-sized B-raf transcript\"\n\n\"Specificity of the antiserum was tested with Western blotting.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5479" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

